Package uno.card

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CascadableCard
    A cascadable card is a card that its action can be cascaded if applied on each other.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActionCard
    Represents an action card in Uno game.
    Card
    Represents a card in Uno game.
    ColoredCard
    A colored card in Uno game, that is cards that have a color.
    Draw2
    Draw 2 or 2+ card of Uno game, that is an action card that when applied, forces next player to pick two cards from store and lose turn.
    NumericCard
    A numeric card of the Uno game, that is a colored card with a number in range [0-9].
    Reverse
    A reverse card that is an action card and reverses the game rotation.
    Skip
    Skip card of the Uno game, that skips next players turn.
    WildCard
    Represents wild cards of the Uno game.
    WildColor
    Wild color card of the Uno game, that changes ground color by player's will.
    WildDraw
    Wild draw card of the Uno game, that changes the color of the ground by player's will, forces next player to pick 4 cards from store and skips its turn.
